<p class="content"><acronym>MONICET</acronym> is scientific research project that aims to obtain more information about the distribution and populations of cetaceans in the Azores, and help to conserve the European and Worldwide cetacean populations. The project itself is based on the comunication between the Whale and Dolphin Watching touristic operations and the researchers, creating standard methodologies to obtain a valuable database. The first two years pretend to be a starting point in order to create a Long Term Database, that will be an important tool to understand better the cetacean dinamics of the Azores archipelago.</p>
